<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>19-306</num>
  <heading>Children to share equally.</heading>
  <text>When the intestate leaves children and no other descendants, the surplus is divided equally among them.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="Pub. L. 89-183" type="History">Sept. 14, 1965, 79 Stat. 698, Pub. L. 89-183, § 1</annotation>
